==English==

===Adjective===
'''Syracusan'''
# Of or belonging to Syracuse, a city in [[Sicily]], [[Italy]], or of the city of Syracuse in central [[New York|New York State]].
#:Ex. ''The Syracusan expedition was the deathblow of the [[Athens|Athenian]] Empire.'' (John Buchan).

===Noun===
'''Syracusan'''  (''plural:'' '''[[Syracusans]]''')
# A native or inhabitant of Syracuse, Sicily, or of Syracuse, New York.
#:Ex. ''[[Dionysius]]...obliged the '''Syracusans''' to accept his tokens in place of silver coins.'' (William Stanley Jevons)